<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>KOLOS:  It doesn't matter what you believe. They're subject to the laws of the Empire. There's nothing you can say that will change that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>ARCHER:  I haven't been able to say anything.</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Where did you take them? Another ship? A planet? Do you understand what will happen if you don't tell them?</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>ARCHER:  I've a pretty good idea.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I'm offering you a way to save your life.</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Let's say I did co-operate. What would happen to these people?</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>KOLOS:  They would be charged with treason.</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>ARCHER:  And end up in a court like this one? Tell the magistrate I'm going to pass on his offer.</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Only a fool would sacrifice himself for people he barely knows.</td></tr>

<tr id="L150"><td><a href="#L150">150</a></td><td>ARCHER:  I know them well enough. They're good people, and I won't turn them over. If you'd let me testify, tell my side of the story, it might become clear why I helped them. But from what I've seen, you're all perfectly happy to ignore what you don't want to hear.</td></tr>

<tr id="L151"><td><a href="#L151">151</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Don't be so quick to accuse me of sharing their interpretation of the law.</td></tr>

<tr id="L152"><td><a href="#L152">152</a></td><td>ARCHER:  No? What's your interpretation?</td></tr>

<tr id="L153"><td><a href="#L153">153</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I became an Advocate many years ago. They were different times.</td></tr>

<tr id="L154"><td><a href="#L154">154</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Better or worse?</td></tr>

<tr id="L155"><td><a href="#L155">155</a></td><td>KOLOS:  The courts were more willing to listen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L156"><td><a href="#L156">156</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Then maybe you should remind them of those different times. Nothing like a good history lesson.</td></tr>

<tr id="L157"><td><a href="#L157">157</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I'm an old man. Too old to challenge the rules.</td></tr>

<tr id="L158"><td><a href="#L158">158</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Even if your client's life depends on it? I get the feeling you're as frustrated as I am. That you want to stand up to them. But you've given up. You're afraid of them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L159"><td><a href="#L159">159</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I'm not afraid.</td></tr>

<tr id="L160"><td><a href="#L160">160</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Then prove it. Challenge them. Show them what a real trial is like.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Hall of Justice</td></tr>
<tr id="L161"><td><a href="#L161">161</a></td><td>MAGISTRATE:  Strength to the Empire. Have you informed the accused of our offer?</td></tr>

<tr id="L162"><td><a href="#L162">162</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I have.</td></tr>

<tr id="L163"><td><a href="#L163">163</a></td><td>MAGISTRATE:  And does he wish to address this tribunal?</td></tr>

<tr id="L164"><td><a href="#L164">164</a></td><td>KOLOS:  He does. He wishes to testify in his own defence.</td></tr>

<tr id="L165"><td><a href="#L165">165</a></td><td>ORAK:  I object. The time for testimony is over.</td></tr>

<tr id="L166"><td><a href="#L166">166</a></td><td>KOLOS:  With respect, Magistrate, no verdict has been reached.</td></tr>

<tr id="L167"><td><a href="#L167">167</a></td><td>ORAK:  Irrelevant! I urge you to end these proceedings.</td></tr>

<tr id="L168"><td><a href="#L168">168</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I am within my rights to present further testimony.</td></tr>

