<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>MAGISTRATE:  I have weighed the evidence carefully. Advocate Kolos has made an impressive case, much to the surprise of this tribunal. Based upon his arguments I am inclined to believe that the accused was a victim of his own foolishness. He was not fomenting rebellion. But, as Prosecutor Orak has made clear, the laws of the Empire have been violated and Captain Archer must be held accountable for his actions regardless of his intent. I therefore find the accused guilty as charged. (popular acclamation from the galleries) However! However this tribunal cannot ignore his actions assisting the Klingon people. Therefore the sentence of death is commuted. Silence! Jonathan Archer, you are condemned to the dilithium mines on the penal colony of Rura Pente for the remainder of your life. Remove the prisoner.</td></tr>

