<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Honour? You acknowledged that Captain Archer acted with conviction and integrity, and how do you reward him? With this grand public display of compassion before sending him to his death in a frozen cave.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>MAGISTRATE:  Enough!</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Forgive me if I fail to see the honour in that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>MAGISTRATE:  You are in contempt of this tribunal. Since you have such admiration for the prisoner, you will join him on Rura Pente for a period of one year. Remove them both.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Bridge</td></tr>
<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>T'POL:  The Vulcan High Command will continue to lobby for the Captain's release.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>TUCKER:  So what do we do?</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>T'POL:  The Klingons have only allowed us to remain here during the trial. We're to leave immediately.</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>REED:  And abandon the Captain?</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>T'POL:  We don't have a choice.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>TRAVIS:  What's this Rura Pente like?</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>T'POL:  It's quite inhospitable.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>REED:  They're going to have to get there.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>T'POL:  We're deep inside Klingon territory. A rescue attempt is out of the question.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>TUCKER:  I'm willing to risk it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>T'POL:  The Captain isn't. He made it clear he didn't want us to endanger the crew on his behalf.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>TUCKER:  So you're saying we just forget about him?</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>T'POL:  I'm saying a rescue isn't an option, but there are diplomatic channels.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>TUCKER:  We tried diplomatic channels.</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>T'POL:  Not all of them. I've dealt with several Klingon bureaucrats in the past. Some of them can be persuaded. Mister Mayweather, take us out of orbit.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Rura Pente</td></tr>
<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Down inside the ice and snow covered planet, prisoners wearing ragged furs against the cold mine dilithium by hand.</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>GUARD:  You! Get back to work!</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kolos and Archer are hacking at the walls with pickaxes, and Kolos is exhausted.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You all right?</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Perhaps I spent too much time in the law library and not enough in the battlefield.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Not all Klingons are warriors. Remember?</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A guard prods Kolos with a pain stick.</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>GUARD:  Our ships run on dilithium, not talk.</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Leave him alone.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>GUARD:  Get back to work.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: They fight and Archer turns the pain stick on the guard, and gets jabbed himself by a second guard.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>GUARD:  Anymore trouble from you and you'll spend the night on the surface.</td></tr>

<tr id="L357"><td><a href="#L357">357</a></td><td>KOLOS:  You're a fool.</td></tr>

<tr id="L358"><td><a href="#L358">358</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You're welcome.</td></tr>

<tr id="L359"><td><a href="#L359">359</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Haven't you learned your lesson? This is why you were sent here in the first place. For interfering in affairs that have nothing to do with you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L360"><td><a href="#L360">360</a></td><td>ARCHER:  We have a saying on Earth. You don't kick a man when he's down.</td></tr>

<tr id="L361"><td><a href="#L361">361</a></td><td>KOLOS:  So, are all humans like this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L362"><td><a href="#L362">362</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Like what? Fair?</td></tr>

<tr id="L363"><td><a href="#L363">363</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Stupid.</td></tr>

<tr id="L364"><td><a href="#L364">364</a></td><td>ARCHER:  (laughing) It's in our nature.</td></tr>

<tr id="L365"><td><a href="#L365">365</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Stand up. We have work to do, unless you want to sleep on the surface.</td></tr>

<tr id="L366"><td><a href="#L366">366</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Later, as the pair dump some rock into a cart.</td></tr>

<tr id="L367"><td><a href="#L367">367</a></td><td>GUARD [OC]:  Follow me. This way.</td></tr>

<tr id="L368"><td><a href="#L368">368</a></td><td>ARCHER:  New arrivals?</td></tr>

<tr id="L369"><td><a href="#L369">369</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Prosecutor Orak has been busy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L370"><td><a href="#L370">370</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: They return to work, but one of the newcomers leaves the group and approaches Archer. Kolos intercepts him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L371"><td><a href="#L371">371</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Stay away from us. We have nothing you want.</td></tr>

<tr id="L372"><td><a href="#L372">372</a></td><td>REED:  (throwing back hood) Captain.</td></tr>

<tr id="L373"><td><a href="#L373">373</a></td><td>ARCHER:  It's all right. He's from my ship.</td></tr>

<tr id="L374"><td><a href="#L374">374</a></td><td>REED:  It's good to see you, sir.</td></tr>

<tr id="L375"><td><a href="#L375">375</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You, too. Lieutenant Reed, this is Kolos, my Advocate.</td></tr>

<tr id="L376"><td><a href="#L376">376</a></td><td>REED:  Pleasure.</td></tr>

<tr id="L377"><td><a href="#L377">377</a></td><td>ARCHER:  How'd you get here?</td></tr>

<tr id="L378"><td><a href="#L378">378</a></td><td>REED:  T'Pol knows a few Klingon officials from her days in the Ministry of Security. One of them put us in touch with a corrections officer who was willing to look the other way for the right price. I came on one of the dilithium barges. We bribed the captain to bring us here and take us back to Enterprise.</td></tr>

<tr id="L379"><td><a href="#L379">379</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Is there room for one more?</td></tr>

<tr id="L380"><td><a href="#L380">380</a></td><td>REED:  I imagine so, but we have to hurry.</td></tr>

<tr id="L381"><td><a href="#L381">381</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Come on.</td></tr>

<tr id="L382"><td><a href="#L382">382</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I can't go with you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L383"><td><a href="#L383">383</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Why not?</td></tr>

<tr id="L384"><td><a href="#L384">384</a></td><td>KOLOS:  I've been an advocate for fifty years, and I spent the last twenty of them standing in that tribunal playing my part, holding my tongue, and all the while honourable men were being sent to places like this without the benefit of a defence. And then I was assigned your case. You told me that on your world a few courageous people made a difference. I'm not sure I have the courage, but I know I'll never be able to restore honour to my people living as a fugitive.</td></tr>

<tr id="L385"><td><a href="#L385">385</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You realise what that means. You said most prisoners here don't survive a year.</td></tr>

<tr id="L386"><td><a href="#L386">386</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Most prisoners here have very little to live for.</td></tr>

<tr id="L387"><td><a href="#L387">387</a></td><td>REED:  Captain?</td></tr>

<tr id="L388"><td><a href="#L388">388</a></td><td>KOLOS:  Go. Go!</td></tr>

